From: gmonsoon <greataji13@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 02:30:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: qcom: sm8250-retroidpocket: add fan cooling-maps

The pwm-fan driver sets the fan to maximum PWM at probe and, with no
cooling-maps in any thermal zone, nothing ever lowers it again - the
fan runs at 100% forever unless userspace intervenes.

Add active trip points and cooling-maps to the skin-msm-thermal zone
(pm8150l ADC-TM skin sensor) so the kernel thermal governor steps the
fan through its cooling levels (0/32/64/128/255) automatically:
38C -> 32, 43C -> 64, 48C -> 128, 53C -> 255, 3C hysteresis, plus a
70C critical trip. No userspace fan daemon needed.

Tested on Armbian (mainline 6.18) with the same device tree.
---
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8250-retroidpocket-common.dtsi	2026-06-13 02:20:40.963031673 +0700
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/qcom/sm8250-retroidpocket-common.dtsi	2026-06-13 02:20:56.233369768 +0700
@@ -86,10 +86,56 @@
 			thermal-sensors = <&pm8150l_adc_tm 0>;
 
 			trips {
-				active-config0 {
-					temperature = <50000>;
-					hysteresis = <4000>;
-					type = "passive";
+				skin_fan_lvl1: skin-fan-lvl1 {
+					temperature = <38000>;
+					hysteresis = <3000>;
+					type = "active";
+				};
+
+				skin_fan_lvl2: skin-fan-lvl2 {
+					temperature = <43000>;
+					hysteresis = <3000>;
+					type = "active";
+				};
+
+				skin_fan_lvl3: skin-fan-lvl3 {
+					temperature = <48000>;
+					hysteresis = <3000>;
+					type = "active";
+				};
+
+				skin_fan_lvl4: skin-fan-lvl4 {
+					temperature = <53000>;
+					hysteresis = <3000>;
+					type = "active";
+				};
+
+				skin-critical {
+					temperature = <70000>;
+					hysteresis = <1000>;
+					type = "critical";
+				};
+			};
+
+			cooling-maps {
+				map0 {
+					trip = <&skin_fan_lvl1>;
+					cooling-device = <&fan 1 1>;
+				};
+
+				map1 {
+					trip = <&skin_fan_lvl2>;
+					cooling-device = <&fan 2 2>;
+				};
+
+				map2 {
+					trip = <&skin_fan_lvl3>;
+					cooling-device = <&fan 3 3>;
+				};
+
+				map3 {
+					trip = <&skin_fan_lvl4>;
+					cooling-device = <&fan 4 4>;
 				};
 			};
 		};
